    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Doctrinal concept in several mythologies and religion, by which a hero or deity was miraculously conceived by a woman still a virgin. An example is in Christianity, where Christ is believed to have been born of the Virgin Mary. For a natural form of asexual reproduction in in plants and animals, see "parthenogenesis."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
